The Blitzboks will be looking to consolidate their lead on the World Sevens Series points table at this weekend&#8217;s Sydney tournament. And given their rampant form to date, it would take a brave man to bet against them not doing well again. But being favourites also means opponents target you. That&#8217;s why Chris Dry, one of the Blitzboks&#8217; most reliable performers, is wary of becoming complacent. For more sport your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.